Global investors  bought a  net 2.38
billion rupees ($44.3 million) of Indian equity  derivatives  on
Oct. 19, according to the National Stock Exchange.  Open interest, or the number of contracts outstanding in
value terms, fell 0.5 percent to 1.028 trillion rupees,
according to the exchangeâ€™s  website . Open interest reached a
record 1.6 trillion rupees on Sept. 21, 2010.  Foreign funds bought a net 801 million rupees of shares in
the  cash  segment on Oct. 19, according to preliminary data given
